Overview
A simple calculator implemented in Perl that handles basic arithmetic operations and variable assignments. This implementation features expression evaluation with support for variables in a simple REPL interface.

Features
Basic Arithmetic: Supports +, -, *, / operations

Variables: Store and recall values using variables

Error Handling: Basic error detection for invalid expressions

Interactive REPL: Read-Evaluate-Print Loop interface

HOW TO USE 

Copy and paste the entire code into https://www.tutorialspoint.com/execute_perl_online.php
Execute it.